cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

The paper proposes an architecture for deep neural networks with hidden layer branches that learn targets of lower hierarchy than final layer targets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it deals with neural networks and learning. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed architecture to a text classification task, which falls under the sub-categories of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of hidden layer branches also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the text classification task may involve the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) or recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing tasks.
